source.name: Archival Research Catalog (ARC) Archival Descriptions
source.description: The Archival Research Catalog (ARC) data set provides archival descriptions of the permanent holdings of the federal government in the custody of the National Archives and Records administration. The archival descriptions include information on traditional paper holdings, logical data records (electronic records), and artifacts.
